NOMINATIONS  TO  THE  DEPARTMENT  OF 

TRANSPORTATION 

TUESDAY,  APRIL  26,  2005

COMMITTEE ON COMMERCE, SCIENCE, AND TRANSPORTATION, 

U.S. SENATE, 

Washington, DC. 

The  Committee  met,  pursuant  to  notice,  at  10:03  a.m.  in  room 
SR–253,  Russell  Senate  Office  Building,  Hon.  Ted  Stevens,
Chairman of the Committee, presiding. 

OPENING STATEMENT OF HON. TED STEVENS,

U.S. SENATOR FROM ALASKA 

The  CHAIRMAN.  While  we  are  waiting  for  our  Co-Chairman,  let 
me  thank  you  all  for  coming.  Perhaps  we  could  have  an  oppor-
tunity  to  have  the  two  nominees  introduce  their  family  who  are 
here. Ms. Scheinberg, would you like to tell us who is with you for 
the record today. 

Ms.  SCHEINBERG.  Thank  you,  Senator.  I  would  like  to  introduce: 
my  father,  Jacob  Factor;  my  husband,  David  Turner;  and  my  son, 
Eric Turner. 

The  CHAIRMAN.  Thank  you  very  much.  It  is  nice  to  have  you 

Ms. Cino, I understand you have——
Ms. CINO. I have my Northern Virginia family here. 
The CHAIRMAN. It is a notorious family you brought with you this 

here. 

