volved  as  a  party  in  an  administrative  agency  proceeding  or  civil  litigation?  If  so, 
please explain.

While  serving  as  Executive  Director  of  the  National  Republican  Congressional 
Committee  (01/1993–03/1997)  and  as  Deputy  Chairman  of  the  Republican  Na-
tional  Committee  (06/2003–04/2005),  complaints  were  lodged  against  the  Com-
mittees by the Federal Election Commission. 
It  is  very  common  to  have  political  organizations  file  complaints  with  the  Fed-
eral  Election  Commission,  especially  during  an  election  year.  The  National  Re-
publican  Congressional  Committee  and  the  Republican  National  Committee, 
likewise file complaints against other political organizations.

