30

One  example  of  where  that  is  already  being  done  is  in  the  Air  Traffic  Organiza-
tion,  which  is  establishing  unit  cost  metrics  to  help  drive  efficiencies  within  the  or-
ganization.  The  recently  published  ATO  Annual  Performance  Report  to  Congress 
noted that FY 2004 costs per flight fell an estimated $17. The support for this num-
ber came directly from the FAA Cost Accounting System.

